---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About Khaled Zaky — Senior Director of Agentic AI Platform Engineering at RBC Borealis.">
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">

    <!-- Intro / Hero -->
    <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-10 mb-14">
      <img
        src="/img/khaled.png"
        alt="Khaled Zaky"
        class="w-48 h-48 rounded-2xl object-cover shadow-lg shrink-0"
      />
      <div>
        <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-gray-900 dark:text-white font-serif mb-3">
          About me
        </h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-3">
          I build secure platforms across identity, cloud, and agentic AI.
        </p>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium rounded-full bg-primary-100 text-primary-700 dark:bg-primary-900/30 dark:text-primary-400">
          Senior Director, Agentic AI Platform Engineering at RBC Borealis
        </span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Main Bio -->
    <div class="prose dark:prose-invert prose-lg max-w-none mb-14">
      <p>
        Senior technology and product leader with 12+ years of experience designing and operating large-scale cloud, identity, and platform systems in highly regulated environments. Currently a Senior Director at <strong><a href="https://rbcborealis.com">RBC Borealis AI</a></strong>, focused on building foundational platform capabilities that enable secure, governed adoption of AI and agent-based systems across the enterprise.
      </p>

      <p>
        His work spans platform architecture, identity integration, orchestration patterns, observability, and governance — partnering closely with Global Security, IAM, and Enterprise Architecture to ensure designs align with enterprise identity, security, and regulatory expectations.
      </p>

      <p>
        Previously, Khaled was a Senior Product Manager, Technical at <a href="https://aws.amazon.com">Amazon Web Services (AWS)</a>, where he was the technical owner for product strategy across AWS sign-in security, MFA, passkeys, and credential risk. He led the design and launch of passkeys and multiple MFA devices for AWS IAM, and played a key role in root MFA enforcement initiatives. He served as Amazon's representative on the <a href="https://fidoalliance.org/">FIDO Alliance</a> board and contributed to the <a href="https://www.w3.org/groups/wg/webauthn/">W3C WebAuthn Working Group</a>, with published work on enterprise authentication standards.
      </p>

      <p>
        Before AWS, Khaled was Director of Product Management for Cloud & Transformation at <a href="https://www.rbc.com">RBC</a>, where he owned strategy and roadmap for the bank's enterprise cloud platform, led cloud, infrastructure, and AIOps product teams, and introduced cloud control objectives aligned with OSFI and internal risk requirements. Prior to that, he held product and architecture roles at <a href="https://www.td.com">TD Bank</a> and <a href="https://www.rogers.com">Rogers Communications</a>, and began his career in software development at <a href="https://www.blackberry.com">BlackBerry</a>, Siemens, and McMaster University.
      </p>

      <p>
        He also teaches at <a href="https://www.coursereport.com/blog/learn-from-a-real-product-manager-at-brainstation-khaled-zaky">BrainStation</a>, where he mentors future product leaders and helps them apply technical, security, and AI concepts to real-world product challenges.
      </p>

      <p>
        At his core, Khaled is driven by a mission to make intelligent and secure systems more accessible — combining usability, trust, and innovation at scale.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Education & Credentials -->
    <section class="mb-14">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-6">Education & Credentials</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-6">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white text-sm">BEng, Software Engineering</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">McMaster University, 2014</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white text-sm">Enterprise Product Management</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">Ted Rogers MBA, Toronto Metropolitan University, 2016</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
        <span class="px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium rounded-full bg-gray-100 text-gray-600 dark:bg-gray-800 dark:text-gray-400">P.Eng</span>
        <span class="px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium rounded-full bg-gray-100 text-gray-600 dark:bg-gray-800 dark:text-gray-400">AWS Certified Architect</span>
        <span class="px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium rounded-full bg-gray-100 text-gray-600 dark:bg-gray-800 dark:text-gray-400">AWS Certified Cloud Practitioner</span>
        <span class="px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium rounded-full bg-gray-100 text-gray-600 dark:bg-gray-800 dark:text-gray-400">CIDPRO Foundation</span>
        <span class="px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium rounded-full bg-gray-100 text-gray-600 dark:bg-gray-800 dark:text-gray-400">Certified Scrum Product Owner</span>
        <span class="px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium rounded-full bg-gray-100 text-gray-600 dark:bg-gray-800 dark:text-gray-400">FIDO Alliance</span>
        <span class="px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium rounded-full bg-gray-100 text-gray-600 dark:bg-gray-800 dark:text-gray-400">W3C WebAuthn</span>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Divider -->
    <hr class="border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 mb-14" />

    <!-- Current Focus Areas -->
    <section class="mb-14">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-6">Current focus areas</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-3">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-900/50">
          <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-primary-500 shrink-0"></span>
          <span class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Agentic AI platforms</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-900/50">
          <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-primary-500 shrink-0"></span>
          <span class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Identity and authentication</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-900/50">
          <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-primary-500 shrink-0"></span>
          <span class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Cloud and distributed systems</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-900/50">
          <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-primary-500 shrink-0"></span>
          <span class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Product strategy and platform design</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-900/50">
          <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-primary-500 shrink-0"></span>
          <span class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Usable security and developer experience</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- How I Work -->
    <section class="mb-14">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-6">How I work</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-3">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <span class="mt-1.5 w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-gray-400 dark:bg-gray-600 shrink-0"></span>
          <span class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Start with customer and operational reality</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <span class="mt-1.5 w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-gray-400 dark:bg-gray-600 shrink-0"></span>
          <span class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Treat security and usability as design constraints, not tradeoffs</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <span class="mt-1.5 w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-gray-400 dark:bg-gray-600 shrink-0"></span>
          <span class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Prefer clear platform primitives over one-off solutions</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <span class="mt-1.5 w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-gray-400 dark:bg-gray-600 shrink-0"></span>
          <span class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Write to clarify decisions and align teams</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <span class="mt-1.5 w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-gray-400 dark:bg-gray-600 shrink-0"></span>
          <span class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Build iteratively with strong feedback loops</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Divider -->
    <hr class="border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 mb-14" />

    <!-- About This Site -->
    <section class="mb-14">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-6">About this site</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-8">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
          <span class="mt-1.5 w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-400 dark:bg-gray-600 shrink-0"></span>
          A living archive of what I'm learning and building
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
          <span class="mt-1.5 w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-400 dark:bg-gray-600 shrink-0"></span>
          Notes and essays on platform design, identity, and AI
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
          <span class="mt-1.5 w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-400 dark:bg-gray-600 shrink-0"></span>
          A sandbox to practice modern tools and publish in public
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Technical details</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">
        <li>Designed and coded on a <a href="http://www.apple.com/macbook-air" class="text-primary-600 dark:text-primary-400 hover:underline">Mac</a></li>
        <li>Built with <a href="https://astro.build" class="text-primary-600 dark:text-primary-400 hover:underline">Astro</a> and <a href="https://tailwindcss.com" class="text-primary-600 dark:text-primary-400 hover:underline">Tailwind CSS</a></li>
        <li>Coded in <a href="https://windsurf.com" class="text-primary-600 dark:text-primary-400 hover:underline">Windsurf</a> and <a href="https://code.visualstudio.com" class="text-primary-600 dark:text-primary-400 hover:underline">Visual Studio Code</a></li>
        <li>Source code hosted on <a href="https://github.com/kzaky/khaledzaky.com" class="text-primary-600 dark:text-primary-400 hover:underline">GitHub</a></li>
        <li>Deployed with <a href="https://aws.amazon.com/codebuild/" class="text-primary-600 dark:text-primary-400 hover:underline">AWS CodeBuild</a>, where site generation runs on each push to GitHub</li>
        <li>Hosted on <a href="https://aws.amazon.com" class="text-primary-600 dark:text-primary-400 hover:underline">AWS</a> using <a href="https://aws.amazon.com/s3/" class="text-primary-600 dark:text-primary-400 hover:underline">Amazon S3</a> for object storage</li>
        <li>Served through <a href="https://aws.amazon.com/cloudfront/" class="text-primary-600 dark:text-primary-400 hover:underline">Amazon CloudFront</a> for content distribution</li>
        <li>Secured with an SSL/TLS certificate from <a href="https://aws.amazon.com/certificate-manager/" class="text-primary-600 dark:text-primary-400 hover:underline">AWS Certificate Manager</a></li>
        <li>Blog posts are researched and drafted with the help of an AI agent powered by <a href="https://aws.amazon.com/bedrock/" class="text-primary-600 dark:text-primary-400 hover:underline">Amazon Bedrock</a></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

  </section>
</BaseLayout>
